The paper focuses on benchmarking simulated robotic manipulation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the use of a real-world dataset and the application of various metrics suggest a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the simulation environments, which further supports the inclusion of cs.LG (machine learning) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also touches on the control and system dynamics of the simulated robots, which could fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
